				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in libnbd. The client did not always correctly verify the NBD server's certificate when using TLS to connect to an NBD server. This issue allows a man-in-the-middle attack on NBD traffic. \n            STATEMENT: This CVE is rated as Moderate because it requires an active Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) attacker who can intercept and modify the connection's traffic at the TCP/IP layer. While this can compromise the confidentiality and integrity of resources, the vulnerability is considered to be difficult to exploit under normal circumstances.",
